{
  "text": "Cos-7 cells (ATCC, Manassas, VA) were cultured in DMEM (Life Technologies-BRL, Grand Island, NY) supplemented with 10% heatinactivated FCS. On the night before transfection, cells were plated at 2 \u03eb 10 5 cells/well. Cells in each well were transfected with 1 g of pMTV-Luc, 2 g of MR receptor plasmid, and 5 ng of pSV2, using cationic liposomes (Lipofectamine-2000; Life Technologies), after which cells were incubated in DMEM supplemented with 10% FCS overnight. Cells were washed, and then serum-free DMEM that contained aldosterone was added. The cells were incubated for an additional 16 h before assay. Luciferase and \u2424-galactosidase activities were measured as described previously [CITATION_1] . Luciferase activity was normalized to \u2424-galactosidase activity to correct for transfection efficiency and is expressed as a percentage of the wild-type receptor activity at 1 nM aldosterone. All results are the mean of at least nine independent transfections. Statistical comparisons are by the Mann-Whitney U test.",
  "citation_candidates": [
